.Nm VisiData
.Nd a terminal utility for exploring and arranging tabular data
.
.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.
.Bl -inset -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact
.It Ic vd
.Op <options>
<input> ...
.
.It <command> | 
.Sy vd
.Op <options>


.It Ic vd
.Op <options>
.Sy Fl -play No <cmdlog>
.Op Fl -batch
.Op Fl -delay No <delay>
.Op Fl o No <output>
--
.Op Fl "-<field>=<value> ..."
.El
.Bl -inset -offset xx -compact
.It Python format strings (like \&"{ Ns Ar field Ns }\&") No are replaced with the Ar value No given on the command line.  
.It These format options must be specified after the --.
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.
.Nm VisiData
.No is a multipurpose tool for exploring, cleaning, editing, and restructuring data from Sx SUPPORTED SOURCES Ns .
Rows can be selected, filtered, and grouped; columns can be rearranged, transformed, and derived via regex or Python expressions; workflows can be documented, communicated, and replayed via the commandlog.
.Nm VisiData No is built on the
.Sy vdtui No platform.
.
.Sh REPLAY MODE
.Bl -tag -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact
.It Fl "p, --play" Ar cmdlog No
.No replays a saved Ar cmdlog No within the interface.
.
.It Fl -batch
replays in batch mode (with no interface and all output to stdout)
.
.It Fl -delay Ar seconds
.No delays Ar seconds No between commands
.
.It Fl "o, --output" Ar file No
.No saves the final visible sheet to Ar file No (as .tsv) at the end of the replay

.It Sy While Replaying
.El
.Bl -tag -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact -offset XXX
.It Sy ^U
pauses/resumes replay
.It Sy Space
executes next row in the replaying sheet
.El
