.Sh Custom Settings
At the start of every session, 
.Nm VisiData No looks for, in order, Sy .visidatarc No in the current directory, Sy $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/visidata/config Ns , or Sy $HOME/.visidatarc Ns , and calls Python exec() on its contents.  Usually used to create command aliases and set persistent options.  For example:
.Bd -literal
globalCommand('0', 'gh')   # goes to first column like vim
options.min_memory_mb=100  # stop processing without 100MB free
